{"title_page": "Eric Blackwood (musician)", "text_new": "{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}{{short description|American singer-songwriter}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name        = Eric Blackwood\n|image       = Eric Blackwood.jpg\n|caption     = at Marillion Weekend, Port Zelande, 2013\n|background  = solo_singer\n|alias       =\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1968|7|24}}<br />{{nowrap|[[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States}}\n|instrument  = Vocals, guitar, keyboards, drums\n|genre       = [[Neo-prog]], [[progressive rock]], [[hard rock]]\n|occupation  = Singer-songwriter, musician, author, special FX technician, property technician, photographer\n|years_active = 1982\u2013present\n|label        = Random Disturbance Records, Wreckords Records, Racket Records, [[Thunder Bay Press]], [[Baker & Taylor]]\n|associated_acts = [[Edison's Children]], Crimson Steele, Sunblister, Blackwood & Foti, [[Marillion]]\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.edisonschildren.com}}, {{URL|http://www.digitalballparks.com}}\n}}\n'''Eric Blackwood''' (also known as '''Eric Pastore''') is an American singer-songwriter, guitarist and musician with the Progressive Rock band '''[[Edison's Children]]''' featuring Progressive Rock Bassist star '''[[Pete Trewavas]]''' of [[Marillion]] and '''Rick Armstrong''' the son of Apollo 11 Mission Commander and 1st Man on the Moon '''[[Neil Armstrong]]'''. Eric is also an author, photographer, webmaster, special FX technician and property technician. He has been an honorary member of the [[Marillion]] touring crew since 2005 and appears as such in the credits on [[Marillion]]'s CDs and DVDs of \"Their Montreal Weekend Concert Series\" in 2009, 2011 and March 2013.\n\nEric was born in Brooklyn New York as the last of 4 children and raised in [[Great Kills]] [[Staten Island]] in [[New York City]]. He graduated from [[New Dorp High School]] in 1986.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newdorphs.org/apps/directory/directory_item.jsp?REC_ID=349202 |title=Alumni Directory: Mr. Eric J. Pastore |publisher=New Dorp High School |accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> He is the brother of former musician Sonny Pastore of \"The Reluctant Reasons\" (who opened for [[The Byrds]] in the late 60's in Europe) and brother of actor [[Garry Pastore]] who has been featured in 3 seasons of HBO's ''[[The Deuce (TV series)|The Deuce]]'' as \"Matty The Horse\", [[Goodfellas]], [[The Sopranos]], [[Carlito's Way]], [[A Bronx Tale]], [[Donnie Brasco (film)|Donnie Brasco]] and [[The Wolf of Wall Street (2013 film)|The Wolf of Wall Street]] and is cousin to [[Vincent Pastore]] of [[The Sopranos]].\n\nBlackwood and [[Pete Trewavas]] (of [[Marillion]] and [[Transatlantic (band)|Transatlantic]]) originally formed the [[progressive rock]] duo [[Edison's Children]] in 2008 and recorded the album ''In The Last Waking Moments...'', released on November 11, 2011, by Random Disturbance Records, and distributed in Europe by Marillion's Racket Records. It spawned the U.S commercial radio Top 40 hit \"A Million Miles Away (I Wish I Had A Time Machine)\" on the FMQB Hot A/C Commercial Radio Charts on September 18, 2012, and remaining in the Top 40 for ten straight weeks, returning to its peak position at number 32 on October 12, 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16693 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-12-11 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215055320/http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16693 |archivedate=December 15, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Blackwood and Trewavas collaborated on more than 100 songs for films and for [[Edison's Children]] between 2008 and 2012. This led to a 2nd [[Edison's Children]] album \"The Final Breath Before November\" which was released in 2013 featuring Pete Trewavas and award winning drummer Henry Rogers. Rick Armstrong, son of Neil Armstrong... 1st Man on the Moon and Mission Commander to Apollo 11 joined as a Synth Guitarist, Lead Guitarist and Bassist in Montreal in 2011 when Edison's Children played their first ever concert with Eric and Pete together. Rick Armstrong stayed on as a permanent member ... finishing up the third album of new material \"Somewhere Between Here and There \" which included new mixes by [[King Crimson]]'s [[Jakko Jakszyk]] of songs from The Final Breath Before November. The song \"At Night\", penned during his previous effort ''Blackwood and Foti'', and remixed by the band Closenuf, has received an Official Grammy Ballot Placement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://closenuf.netfirms.com/GrammyNotice.pdf |title=Best Pop Performance By A Duo Or Group With Vocals |publisher=Closenuf.netfirms.com |accessdate=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304120609/http://closenuf.netfirms.com/GrammyNotice.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nBlackwood stopped recording and performing from all projects in 2013 after a devastating injury left him disabled while working on [[James Gandolfini]]'s final film. He also became stricken with [[Lyme disease]] which led to him being tethered to an IV for over a year. [[Edison's Children]] had been on hiatus since, but Rick Armstrong who had already finished up their 3rd CD \"Somewhere Between Here and There\" and has been a major supporter of the band has begun working on all of [[Edison's Children]]'s back catalog in an attempt to see Eric and Pete's writings finally come to fruition after Eric's injuries had curtailed the band for several years.\n\nAs webmaster and photographer of the website Digitalballparks.com,<ref>http://www.digitalballparks.com</ref> Blackwood authored and photographed the top-selling book ''500 Ballparks'' ([[Thunder Bay Press]], [[Baker & Taylor]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thunderbaybooks.com/PublicStore/catalog/ProductSearch.aspx?sj=172 |title=Product Search - Thunder Bay Press |publisher=Thunderbaybooks.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826153429/http://www.thunderbaybooks.com/PublicStore/catalog/ProductSearch.aspx?sj=172 |archive-date=August 26, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> with his wife, photographer Wendy Farrell.\n\n===Discography===\n*[[Edison's Children]] - Somewhere Between Here and There (Edison's Children's 3rd Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - The Final Breath Before November (Edison's Children's 2nd Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The Last Waking Moments... (Edison's Children's 1st Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The First Waking Moments... (\"The Making Of In The Last Waking Moment's\" - Rare only 500 copies printed)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - A Million Miles Away (I Wish I Had A Time Machine) - EP Single featuring 4 new Edison's Children songs\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The Last Waking Moments - Single EP (EP Single featuring 1 new Edison's Children songs and 2 live tracks)\n*[[DeStressed]] - Soundtrack from the movie\n*[[Growing Down in Brooklyn]] - Soundtrack from the movie\n*Sunblister - Simantik\n*Sunblister - Sunblister (Self titled debut)\n*Blackwood and Foti - Haunted Memories\n\n===Filmograpy===\nEric Blackwood has performed as a Special FX Technician with the KFX Special FX team as well as an On-Set Property Technician and On Set Dresser in over 100 films and television and worked with many of the industry's biggest stars including:\n\n==Feature films==\n*''[[Spider-Man 3]]'' starring [[Tobey Maguire]]\n*''[[American Gangster (film)|American Gangster]]'' starring [[Russell Crowe]], [[Denzel Washington]] and [[Josh Brolin]]\n*''[[The Bourne Ultimatum (film)|Bourne Ultimatum]]'' starring [[Matt Damon]]\n*''[[The Adjustment Bureau]] starring [[Matt Damon]] and [[Emily Blunt]]''\n*''[[I Am Legend (film)|I Am Legend]]'' starring [[Will Smith]]\n*''[[Men In Black 3]]'' starring [[Will Smith]] [[Tommy Lee Jones]] and [[Josh Brolin]]\n*''[[What Happens in Vegas|What Happens In Vegas]]'' starring [[Ashton Kutcher]] and [[Cameron Diaz]]\n*''[[Baby Mama (film)|Baby Mama]]'' starring [[Tina Fey]] and [[Amy Poehler]]\n*''[[Salt (2010 film)|Salt]]'' starring [[Angelina Jolie]] and [[Liev Schreiber]]\n*''[[Wanted (2008 film)|Wanted]]'' starring [[Angelina Jolie]] and [[Morgan Freeman]]\n*''[[Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief|Percy Jackson and The Olympians: The Lightning Thief]]''\n*''[[Friends with Benefits (film)|Friends With Benefits]]'' starring [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Mila Kunis]] and [[Woody Harrelson]]\n*''[[Violet & Daisy|Violet and Daisy]]'' starring [[James Gandolfini]] and [[Saoirse Ronan]]\n*''[[The Drop (film)|The Drop]]'' starring [[James Gandolfini]] and [[Tom Hardy]]\n*''[[The Back-up Plan]]'' starring [[Jennifer Lopez]]\n*[[Guy Ritchie]]'s ''[[Sherlock Holmes (2009 film)|Sherlock Holmes]]'' starring [[Jude Law]] and [[Robert Downey Jr.]]\n*[[Kevin Smith]]'s ''[[Cop Out (2010 film)|Cop Out]]'' starring [[Bruce Willis]] and [[Tracy Morgan]]\n*[[Nora Ephron]]'s ''[[Julie & Julia|Julie and Julia]]'' starring [[Meryl Streep]], [[Amy Adams]] and [[Stanley Tucci]]\n*[[Oprah Winfrey]]'s ''[[Oprah Winfrey Presents: Mitch Albom's For One More Day|For One More Day]]'' starring [[Michael Imperioli]]\n*[[Oliver Stone]]'s ''[[World Trade Center (film)|World Trade Center]]'' starring [[Nicolas Cage]]\n*[[Darren Aronofsky]]'s ''[[The Wrestler (2008 film)|The Wrestler]]'' starring [[Mickey Rourke]], [[Mickey Rourke]], [[Marisa Tomei]] and [[Evan Rachel Wood]]\n*[[Darren Aronofsky]]'s ''[[Black Swan (film)|Black Swan]]'' starring [[Natalie Portman]], [[Mila Kunis]] and [[Winona Ryder]]\n*''[[The Taking of Pelham One Two Three (1998 film)|The Taking of Pelham 1-2-3]]'' starring [[Donnie Wahlberg]] and [[Edward James Olmos]]\n*''[[The Other Guys]]'' starring [[Will Ferrell]], [[Samuel L. Jackson]] and [[Mark Wahlberg]]\n*''[[August Rush]]'' starring [[Robin Williams]] and [[Jonathan Rhys Meyers]]\n*''[[Mr. Popper's Penguins (film)|Mr. Popper's Penguins]]'' starring [[Jim Carrey]]\n*''[[Perfect Stranger (film)|Perfect Stranger]]'' starring [[Bruce Willis]] and [[Halle Berry]]\n*''[[Assassination of a High School President]]'' starring [[Bruce Willis]] and [[Mischa Barton]]\n*''[[A Walk Among the Tombstones (film)|A Walk Among The Tombstones]]'' starring [[Liam Neeson]]\n*''[[The Hoax]]'' starring [[Richard Gere]], [[Alfred Molina]] and [[Stanley Tucci]]\n*''[[The Rebound]]'' starring [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]]\n<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2424711/</ref>\n\n==Television==\n*[[J. J. Abrams]]' ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]'' starring [[Michael Emerson]] (of Lost fame), [[Jim Caviezel]] and [[Taraji P. Henson]]\n*''[[Boardwalk Empire]]'' (HBO) starring [[Steve Buscemi]], [[Bobby Cannavale]] and [[Michael Shannon]]\n*''[[Rescue Me (American TV series)|Rescue Me]]'' starring [[Denis Leary]]\n*''[[30 Rock]]'' starring [[Tina Fey]], [[Tracy Morgan]] and [[Alec Baldwin]]\n*''[[Smash (U.S. TV series)|Smash]]'' starring [[Debra Messing]] and [[Katherine McPhee]]\n*[[Dick Wolf]]'s ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit|Law and Order: SVU]]''\n*[[Dick Wolf]]'s ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent|Law and Order: Criminal Intent]]''\n*[[Dick Wolf]]'s ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent|Law and Order: Trial By Jury]]''\n*''[[CSI: NY]]'' starring [[Gary Sinise]]\n*''[[Kings (American TV series)|Kings]]'' Starring [[Ian McShane]]\n*''[[White Collar (TV series)|White Collar]]'' starring [[Matt Bomer]] and [[Tim DeKay]]\n*''[[America's Next Top Model]]'' starring [[Tyra Banks]]\n*''[[New Amsterdam]]'' starring [[Nikolaj Coster-Waldau]] (of Game of Thrones)\n*''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2424711/</ref>\n\n==Consultant==\n*''[[42 (film)|42: The Jackie Robinson Story]]'' starring [[Chadwick Boseman]] and [[Harrison Ford]] - Baseball Stadium Expert and Locations Advisor\n<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2424711/</ref>\n\n==Music Director==\n*''[[DeStressed]]'' - with [[Pete Trewavas]] and [[Edison's Children]] starring [[Garry Pastore]]\n*''[[Growing Down In Brooklyn]]'' starring [[Vincent Pastore]] and [[Garry Pastore]]\n<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2424711/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Blackwood, Eric}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American singer-songwriters]]\n", "text_old": "{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}{{short description|American singer-songwriter}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2011}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name        = Eric Blackwood\n|image       = Eric Blackwood.jpg\n|caption     = at Marillion Weekend, Port Zelande, 2013\n|background  = solo_singer\n|alias       =\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1968|7|24}}<br />{{nowrap|[[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States}}\n|instrument  = Vocals, guitar, keyboards, drums\n|genre       = [[Neo-prog]], [[progressive rock]], [[hard rock]]\n|occupation  = Singer-songwriter, musician, author, special FX technician, property technician, photographer\n|years_active = 1982\u2013present\n|label        = Random Disturbance Records, Wreckords Records, Racket Records, [[Thunder Bay Press]], [[Baker & Taylor]]\n|associated_acts = [[Edison's Children]], Crimson Steele, Sunblister, Blackwood & Foti, [[Marillion]]\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.edisonschildren.com}}, {{URL|http://www.digitalballparks.com}}\n}}\n'''Eric Blackwood''' (also known as '''Eric Pastore''') is an American singer-songwriter, guitarist and musician with the Progressive Rock band '''[[Edison's Children]]''' featuring Progressive Rock Bassist star '''[[Pete Trewavas]]''' of [[Marillion]] and '''Rick Armstrong''' the son of Apollo 11 Mission Commander and 1st Man on the Moon '''[[Neil Armstrong]]'''. Eric is also an author, photographer, webmaster, special FX technician and property technician. He has been an honorary member of the [[Marillion]] touring crew since 2005 and appears as such in the credits on [[Marillion]]'s CDs and DVDs of \"Their Montreal Weekend Concert Series\" in 2009, 2011 and March 2013.\n\nEric was born in Brooklyn New York as the last of 4 children and raised in [[Great Kills]] [[Staten Island]] in [[New York City]]. He graduated from [[New Dorp High School]] in 1986.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newdorphs.org/apps/directory/directory_item.jsp?REC_ID=349202 |title=Alumni Directory: Mr. Eric J. Pastore |publisher=New Dorp High School |accessdate=November 18, 2019}}</ref> He is brother of former musician Sonny Pastore of \"The Reluctant Reasons\" (who opened for [[The Byrds]] in the late 60's in Europe) and brother of actor [[Garry Pastore]] who has been featured in 3 seasons of HBO's ''[[The Deuce (TV series)|The Deuce]]'' as \"Matty The Horse\", [[Goodfellas]], [[The Sopranos]], [[Carlito's Way]], [[A Bronx Tale]], [[Donnie Brasco (film)|Donnie Brasco]] and [[The Wolf of Wall Street (2013 film)|The Wolf of Wall Street]] and is cousin to [[Vincent Pastore]] of [[The Sopranos]].\n\nBlackwood and [[Pete Trewavas]] (of [[Marillion]] and [[Transatlantic (band)|Transatlantic]]) originally formed the [[progressive rock]] duo [[Edison's Children]] in 2008 and recorded the album ''In The Last Waking Moments...'', released on November 11, 2011, by Random Disturbance Records, and distributed in Europe by Marillion's Racket Records. It spawned the U.S commercial radio Top 40 hit \"A Million Miles Away (I Wish I Had A Time Machine)\" on the FMQB Hot A/C Commercial Radio Charts on September 18, 2012, and remaining in the Top 40 for ten straight weeks, returning to its peak position at number 32 on October 12, 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16693 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-12-11 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215055320/http://fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=16693 |archivedate=December 15, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Blackwood and Trewavas collaborated on more than 100 songs for films and for [[Edison's Children]] between 2008 and 2012. This led to a 2nd [[Edison's Children]] album \"The Final Breath Before November\" which was released in 2013 featuring Pete Trewavas and award winning drummer Henry Rogers. Rick Armstrong, son of Neil Armstrong... 1st Man on the Moon and Mission Commander to Apollo 11 joined as a Synth Guitarist, Lead Guitarist and Bassist in Montreal in 2011 when Edison's Children played their first ever concert with Eric and Pete together. Rick Armstrong stayed on as a permanent member ... finishing up the third album of new material \"Somewhere Between Here and There \" which included new mixes by [[King Crimson]]'s [[Jakko Jakszyk]] of songs from The Final Breath Before November. The song \"At Night\", penned during his previous effort ''Blackwood and Foti'', and remixed by the band Closenuf, has received an Official Grammy Ballot Placement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://closenuf.netfirms.com/GrammyNotice.pdf |title=Best Pop Performance By A Duo Or Group With Vocals |publisher=Closenuf.netfirms.com |accessdate=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304120609/http://closenuf.netfirms.com/GrammyNotice.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nBlackwood stopped recording and performing from all projects in 2013 after a devastating injury left him disabled while working on [[James Gandolfini]]'s final film. He also became stricken with [[Lyme disease]] which led to him being tethered to an IV for over a year. [[Edison's Children]] had been on hiatus since, but Rick Armstrong who had already finished up their 3rd CD \"Somewhere Between Here and There\" and has been a major supporter of the band has begun working on all of [[Edison's Children]]'s back catalog in an attempt to see Eric and Pete's writings finally come to fruition after Eric's injuries had curtailed the band for several years.\n\nAs webmaster and photographer of the website Digitalballparks.com,<ref>http://www.digitalballparks.com</ref> Blackwood authored and photographed the top-selling book ''500 Ballparks'' ([[Thunder Bay Press]], [[Baker & Taylor]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thunderbaybooks.com/PublicStore/catalog/ProductSearch.aspx?sj=172 |title=Product Search - Thunder Bay Press |publisher=Thunderbaybooks.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826153429/http://www.thunderbaybooks.com/PublicStore/catalog/ProductSearch.aspx?sj=172 |archive-date=August 26, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> with his wife, photographer Wendy Farrell.\n\n===Discography===\n*[[Edison's Children]] - Somewhere Between Here and There (Edison's Children's 3rd Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - The Final Breath Before November (Edison's Children's 2nd Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The Last Waking Moments... (Edison's Children's 1st Album)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The First Waking Moments... (\"The Making Of In The Last Waking Moment's\" - Rare only 500 copies printed)\n*[[Edison's Children]] - A Million Miles Away (I Wish I Had A Time Machine) - EP Single featuring 4 new Edison's Children songs\n*[[Edison's Children]] - In The Last Waking Moments - Single EP (EP Single featuring 1 new Edison's Children songs and 2 live tracks)\n*[[DeStressed]] - Soundtrack from the movie\n*[[Growing Down in Brooklyn]] - Soundtrack from the movie\n*Sunblister - Simantik\n*Sunblister - Sunblister (Self titled debut)\n*Blackwood and Foti - Haunted Memories\n\n===Filmograpy===\nEric Blackwood has performed as a Special FX Technician with the KFX Special FX team as well as an On-Set Property Technician and On Set Dresser in over 100 films and television and worked with many of the industry's biggest stars including:\n\n==Feature films==\n*''[[Spider-Man 3]]'' starring [[Tobey Maguire]]\n*''[[American Gangster (film)|American Gangster]]'' starring [[Russell Crowe]], [[Denzel Washington]] and [[Josh Brolin]]\n*''[[The Bourne Ultimatum (film)|Bourne Ultimatum]]'' starring [[Matt Damon]]\n*''[[The Adjustment Bureau]] starring [[Matt Damon]] and [[Emily Blunt]]''\n*''[[I Am Legend (film)|I Am Legend]]'' s