eill\n| length7         = 3:55\n| title8          = Station to Station\n| length8         = 8:40\n| title9          = [[Stay (David Bowie song)|Stay]]\n| note9           = Previously unreleased\n| length9         = 7:17\n| title10         = TVC 15\n| length10        = 4:32\n}}\n\n====2017 rerelease track listing====\n\nIn 2017, the album was included, in two versions, in the ''[[A New Career in a New Town (1977\u20131982)]]'' [[box set]] released by Parlophone.  One version contained the original mix and the same list and ordering of tracks that had appeared on the original vinyl album; the other was a new version of the album, based on the 2005 edition but including two previously unreleased songs from the concerts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.davidbowie.com/news/new-career-new-town-1977-1982-57146 |title=A New Career in a New Town (1977\u20131982) |website=David Bowie |date=12 July 2016 |accessdate=21 February 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713014523/http://www.davidbowie.com/news/new-career-new-town-1977-1982-57146 |archivedate=13 July 2017  }}</ref> The latter was also released separately, in 2-CD and 3-LP formats, in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author=Paul Sinclair |date=19 January 2018 |url=http://www.superdeluxeedition.com/news/david-bowie-remastered-berlin-albums-available-separately-next-month |title=David Bowie / Remastered \u2018Berlin\u2019 albums available separately next month |website=Super Deluxe Edition |accessdate=21 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist\n| all_writing     = \n| collapsed       = no\n| headline        =Side one\n| total_length    = 17:37\n| title1 = Warszawa\n| length1 = 6:53\n| title2= \"Heroes\"\n| length2 = 6:19\n| title3 = What in the World\n| length3 = 4:25\n|extra_column=|note1=|writer1=Bowie, Eno|extra1=|note2=|writer2=Bowie, Eno|extra2=|note3=|writer3=|extra3=|note4=|writer4=|extra4=}}{{tracklist\n| all_writing     = \n| collapsed       = no\n| headline        =Side two\n| total_length    = 1